  "issue_number": 226,
  "issue_title": "feat(eval): recall-quality eval harness with labeled query set + CI baseline",
  "issue_body": "**What you're trying to do**\n\ngbrain ships BrainBench scorecards (P@5 49.1%, R@5 97.9%). Vouch has `kb.eval_embeddings` but no labeled-test-set + CI baseline gate. Without one, every retrieval-tier change ships without a quality signal; regressions land silently. Distinct from `proposed-features.md` #8 (latency-only bench).\n\n**Suggested shape**\n\n```bash\nvouch eval recall ./eval/queries.jsonl    # score current retrieval against the set\nvouch eval recall --baseline baseline.json  # compare; non-zero exit on regression > 5%\nvouch eval recall --capture --since 7d > base.jsonl  # capture real queries for grading\n```\n\n- New `src/vouch/eval/recall.py` runs each labeled query through `kb.context`, computes P@k, R@k, MRR, nDCG against the labeled expected ids.\n- `eval/queries.jsonl` fixture in the repo: 50 queries \u00d7 KB fixture, hand-labeled.\n- CI gate (new `.github/workflows/eval.yml`): runs on every PR touching `src/vouch/embeddings/` or `src/vouch/context.py`, fails if P@5 drops > 5% vs the committed `eval/baseline.json`.\n- Optional LLM-as-judge mode (`--judge gpt-4o-mini`) for harder \"did this claim answer the query\" verdicts; opt-in, never default.\n\n**Acceptance**\n\n- `vouch eval recall ./eval/queries.jsonl` produces a deterministic JSON report.\n- A retrieval change that tanks P@5 by 10% fails CI with a clear diff vs the baseline.\n- The labeled-set fixture is itself a vouch KB (claims + sources), so it round-trips through `vouch import-apply`.\n\n**Out of scope**\n\n- A built-in dashboard for the scores (CI-text-output only).\n- Continuous evaluation against real user queries (gbrain has it; depends on `GBRAIN_CONTRIBUTOR_MODE` equivalent).\n\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-17T04:43:22.000Z",
